1) OVERVIEW
This app helps mothers record expressed breast milk (EBM) and shows
day-of-life (DOL) guidance with reference targets. It also lets ward
staff register beds, update baby information, and view daily totals.

------------------------------------------------------------
2) MOTHERS - QUICK START
1. Login with your Bed ID and password.
2. Enter:
   - Volume per Bottle (ml)
   - Number of Bottles
3. Tap "Save Today's Provision".
4. Review:
   - Day of Life (DOL)
   - Current Weight
   - Tailored reminders
   - Today's total and guidance

------------------------------------------------------------
3) MOTHERS - DETAILED GUIDE

Login
- Open the app and enter your ID and password.
- Example ID: CTM01, LKM101, ABC08.
- Case does not matter (bed23 and BED23 are the same).

Baby Information
- Day of Life (DOL) is calculated automatically from the baby's DOB.
- Current weight is shown (if staff has updated it).
- Tailored information appears under Baby Information:
  - DOL 0-3: Tips to increase milk supply
  - DOL 4-7: Guidance about milk coming in and expected volume

Record Today's EBM
- Enter volume per bottle and number of bottles.
- Tap "Save Today's Provision".
- You can update anytime on the same day (it will overwrite previous).

Today's Total and Guidance
- The app calculates the total milk for today.
- If supply meets the reference:
  "You have already done a good job! Keep it up!"
- If supply is below reference, you will see supportive guidance.

Refresh and Logout
- Tap "Refresh" to re-load today's data.
- Tap "Logout" when finished.

------------------------------------------------------------
4) WARD STAFF (ADMIN) - QUICK START
1. Login as admin (HCW) with the staff password.
2. Register new bed OR select an existing bed.
3. Update DOB, weight, and feeding targets.
4. View ward overview table and export data if needed.

------------------------------------------------------------
5) WARD STAFF (ADMIN) - DETAILED GUIDE

Login
- Enter ID: HCW
- Enter the admin password.

Register a New Bed
- Enter Bed ID, password, DOB, and weight.
- Click "Register Bed".

Edit Bed Information
- Select a bed from the dropdown.
- Click the edit button (pencil icon) in the table.
- Update DOB, weight, volume per bottle, and bottles per day.
- Save changes.

Ward Overview
- The table shows:
  - Bed ID
  - Target total
  - Mother's total
  - PDBM required
  - Last updated time
  - Day of Life and weight

Export Data
- Click "Export Today's Data to Excel" to download a CSV file.

Delete Bed
- Select a bed and click "Delete Selected Bed".
  (Use with caution - this permanently removes the bed record.)

------------------------------------------------------------
6) AUTO LOGOUT AND UPDATES

Auto Logout (Security)
- The app logs out automatically after 15 minutes of inactivity.
- Any click, scroll, or typing resets the timer.

Auto Updates
- The app checks for updates and refreshes automatically when a new
  version is detected.

------------------------------------------------------------
7) TIPS AND TROUBLESHOOTING

If you cannot log in
- Check that your ID and password are correct.
- Ensure you are using the correct bed ID.

If baby DOL or weight is missing
- Ask ward staff to update the baby's DOB and weight.

If totals look wrong
- Tap "Refresh".
- Ensure you entered today's volumes correctly.

If the page looks outdated
- Wait a few seconds for auto-refresh.
- If needed, close and reopen the app.

